3D scatterplots

r3js provides some basic functions for doing 3d plots, the main one being plot3js(). This is used similarly to R’s base plot() function, for example:

data3js <- plot3js(
  x = iris$Sepal.Length,
  y = iris$Sepal.Width,
  z = iris$Petal.Length,
  col = rainbow(3)[iris$Species],
  size = 4
)

x <- seq_len(nrow(volcano))
y <- seq_len(ncol(volcano))

# Setup the plot
data3js <- plot3js(
  x = x,
  y = y,
  z = volcano,
  aspect = c(1,1,0.4),
  type = "n",
  show_plot = FALSE
)

# Determine colors
colfn <- colorRamp(topo.colors(10))
rgbcols <- colfn(
  (volcano - min(volcano)) / diff(range(volcano))
)
cols  <- matrix(
  nrow = nrow(volcano),
  ncol = ncol(volcano)
)
cols[] <- apply(
  rgbcols, 1, function(x){ rgb(x[1], x[2], x[2], maxColorValue = 255) }
)
  
# Add the surface
data3js <- surface3js(
  data3js,
  x   = x,
  y   = y,
  z   = volcano,
  col = cols
)
